// =============================================================================
// net/quic/api/mod.vr — High-level pure-Verum QUIC API
// =============================================================================
// Layer: 5 (Network — QUIC)
// Dependencies: core, core.net.{udp, quic, tls13}, core.security.x509
// =============================================================================
//
// User-facing QUIC façade sitting above the pure-Verum transport
// (`core.net.quic.connection_sm`) + TLS 1.3 handshake driver. Mirrors
// the existing intrinsic-backed `core.net.quic.Connection` surface
// so application code can swap between the two with a single import
// change during the co-existence phase (spec §13.1).
//
// Primary user types:
//
//   QuicClient — dial a QUIC server; open bidirectional/unidirectional
//                streams; exchange datagrams (RFC 9221).
//   QuicServer — bind UDP, accept incoming connections, accept()
//                yields a QuicConnection handle per peer.
//   QuicStream — bidirectional or unidirectional byte stream over a
//                live connection.
//
// Module layout:
//
// ```
// core.net.quic.api
// ├── mod.vr             ← this file (re-exports)
// ├── client.vr          — QuicClient (connect → Connection)
// ├── server.vr          — QuicServer (bind → accept)
// └── stream.vr          — QuicStream byte-stream handle
// ```
//
// =============================================================================

module core.net.quic.api;

public module client;
public module server;
public module stream;

public mount .client.{QuicClient, QuicClientOptions, QuicClientError};
public mount .server.{QuicServer, QuicServerOptions, QuicServerError, QuicAccepted};
public mount .stream.{QuicStream, QuicStreamError};
